  },
  {
    question: "Do you work with new home warranties in Milton?",
    answer: "Yes! We work within warranty requirements to provide enhanced waterproofing that doesn't void builder warranties. Many Milton homeowners upgrade their waterproofing while maintaining their new home coverage."
  },
  {
    question: "How does Milton's escarpment clay soil affect basement waterproofing?",
    answer: "Escarpment clay is highly expansive when wet and contracts when dry, creating hydrostatic pressure against foundations. This clay also has poor drainage characteristics, causing water to pool around foundations rather than drain away. We use specialized membrane systems and drainage designs specifically engineered for expansive escarpment clay conditions."
  },
  {
    question: "What causes escarpment groundwater issues in Milton?",
    answer: "The Niagara Escarpment's limestone bedrock creates underground water channels that emerge at various elevations. Properties on or near the escarpment often experience seasonal groundwater surges as water moves through limestone fissures. Our solutions include deep foundation drainage, sump systems designed for high water tables, and specialized waterproofing for below-grade groundwater pressure."
  },
  {
    question: "Do I need a permit for basement waterproofing in Halton Region?",
    answer: "Most exterior waterproofing projects in Milton require a building permit from the Town of Milton. This includes foundation excavation, weeping tile installation, and structural work. Interior waterproofing (interior drainage systems, sump pumps) typically doesn't require permits unless electrical work is involved. We handle all permit applications and inspections as part of our service."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does basement waterproofing cost in Milton?",
    answer: "Exterior waterproofing in Milton costs $145-$280 per linear foot, with typical projects ranging from $13,000-$27,000 depending on foundation depth, soil conditions, and escarpment challenges. Interior drainage systems cost $80-$200 per linear foot. New subdivision homes often need less extensive work ($13,000-$18,000), while heritage Old Milton homes may require more comprehensive solutions ($22,000-$28,000). We provide free detailed quotes."
  },
  {
    question: "Will waterproofing void my Tarion new home warranty?",
    answer: "Professional waterproofing won't void your Tarion warranty if done correctly. We work within Tarion guidelines, ensuring our upgrades complement (not replace) builder-installed systems during the warranty period. Many Milton homeowners enhance their waterproofing while keeping full warranty protection. We provide documentation that satisfies Tarion requirements and can even strengthen warranty claims if you're experiencing water issues."
  },
  {
    question: "When is the best time of year for waterproofing in Milton?",
    answer: "Late spring through fall (May-October) is ideal for exterior waterproofing in Milton. Ground conditions are workable, excavation is easier, and materials cure properly. However, we work year-round with specialized cold-weather techniques when needed. Interior drainage systems can be installed any season. For emergency situations, we provide 24/7 service regardless of weather. Book early for spring/summer as these are our busiest seasons in rapidly-growing Milton."
  }
];

